parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the Takata airbag recall can lead to the risk of serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Owners have received recall notices but have been unable to get the repair done due to parts unavailability
dealerships not knowing when parts will arrive
and manufacturers not providing a timeline for the repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cracked Dashboard and Airbag Deployment Concerns
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked dashboard can interfere with airbag deployment, leading to serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Owners have reported cracks in the dashboard
which can cause the dashboard to shatter and send shards of plastic flying in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An illuminated airbag light can indicate a problem with the airbag system, which can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Owners have reported that the airbag light is illuminated on their dashboard
indicating a problem with the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard can cause sharp edges and flying debris in the event of an airbag deployment, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities. Additionally, the cracking can also obstruct the proper deployment of airbags, rendering them ineffective.

The sudden and repeated power off and on of the electrical system can cause loss of power, loss of control, and accidents, especially at high speeds. This can also lead to distractions and discomfort for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The entire electrical system suddenly powers off and on repeatedly
electric door locks unlock and relock
and the vehicle must be removed from the road and restarted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty temperature control system can cause distractions and discomfort for the driver, potentially leading to accidents. The faulty liftgate can also cause unexpected openings, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The driver-side temperature control stays at maximum heat
hot air comes through even with the AC running
the upper vents must be kept closed
and the driver is extremely uncomfortable and distracted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety issues, including loss of power to critical systems, such as the airbag system, and can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: ABS and other indicator lights come on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuator can cause safety issues, such as inability to exit the vehicle in an emergency, and can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: doors will not lock or unlock with remote or switch
and doors will not lock or unlock when put into gear or back into park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard can cause safety issues, such as airbag deployment problems, and can lead to accidents or injuries.
The failure of the throttle position sensor can cause safety issues, such as loss of engine power, and can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle goes into "reduced engine power" mode
